Fix 2 bugs in the orchestrator extension at /Users/shivam94/.pi/agent/extensions/orchestrator/:

**Bug A - Steps disappear (activity-feed.ts)**
The `addSubstep()` function pushes substeps to `state.steps[state.currentStep]`. After `completeCurrentStep()`, `currentStep` is clamped to `steps.length - 1` (a completed step). Substeps added to completed steps are invisible in rendering because completed steps render as single `✓` line.

Fix: In `addSubstep()`, detect if the current step is completed. If so, create a new step and set it as active before pushing the substep.

```typescript
export function addSubstep(state: ActivityFeedState, label: string): void {
    // If current step is completed, create a new step for fresh substeps
    if (state.currentStep >= 0 && state.currentStep < state.steps.length && state.steps[state.currentStep].completed) {
        addStep(state, label);
        return;
    }
    // ... existing logic
}
```

Also remove the clamp from `completeCurrentStep()` — let `currentStep` stay at `steps.length` so the next `addSubstep` triggers a new step creation. The bounds check in `addSubstep` will handle it.

**Bug B - Live updates freeze (subagent-runner.ts)**
The 80ms render timer dedup strips ALL spinner characters before comparing:
```typescript
const textWithoutSpinner = text.replace(/[⠋⠙⠹⠸⠼⠴⠦⠧⠇⠏]/g, " ");
if (textWithoutSpinner === _lastRenderText) return;
```

This kills spinner animation during long tool executions with no text changes.

Fix: Track the raw text (with spinner) for dedup, but also track spinner frame changes. Simplest fix: always emit when `_spinnerIndex` has changed since last render.

```typescript
let _lastSpinnerIndex = -1;

renderTimer = setInterval(() => {
    const text = renderCombinedProgress(...) || renderActivityFeed(...);
    // Always emit if spinner frame changed or content changed
    if (_spinnerIndex !== _lastSpinnerIndex || text !== _lastRenderText) {
        _lastRenderText = text;
        _lastSpinnerIndex = _spinnerIndex;
        onUpdate?.({ content: [{ type: "text", text }], ... });
    }
}, 80);
```

