## Pi Extension Testing Stack

| Layer | Tool | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| **Unit tests** | `createHarness()` + `FauxResponse` | Simulate LLM without API keys |
| **TUI rendering** | `FakeTerminal` class | Capture writes, assert on rendered text |
| **Interactive** | tmux sessions | E2E with real terminal |
| **Debugging** | `/debug`, `PI_TUI_DEBUG=1`, VS Code | Breakpoints, render logs |

## Key Pattern: `createHarness()`

```typescript
import { createHarness } from "@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent/test/test-harness";

// Simulate LLM response
const harness = createHarness({ responses: ["hello"] });
await harness.session.prompt("hi");

// Capture events
const toolCalls = harness.eventsOfType("tool_call");
```

## Key Pattern: `FakeTerminal`

```typescript
class FakeTerminal implements Terminal {
  columns = 80; rows = 24;
  writes: string[] = [];
  write(data: string) { this.writes.push(data); }
}

// Assert on rendered output
expect(terminal.writes.join("")).toContain("✓ Step 1");
```

## Debug Commands

| Command | What it does |
|---------|--------------|
| `/debug` | Writes TUI state to `~/.pi/agent/pi-debug.log` |
| `PI_TUI_DEBUG=1` | Per-render snapshots to `/tmp/tui/render-*.log` |
| `PI_DEBUG_REDRAW=1` | Logs all redraw triggers |
| `Shift+Ctrl+D` | Triggers debug callback |
| VS Code JS Debugger | Breakpoints in extension code |

## Recommendation

Replace `test-e2e.ts` (RpcClient approach) with `createHarness()` + `FakeTerminal` for deterministic, fast tests. Use tmux only for visual verification.

